[ec94ffd](https://github.com/ocombe/ocLazyLoad/commit/ec94ffd90fb44cd8f8a397efa53fa965b73d44ee): Fix an issue where IE invalidates any elements saved during compilation by adding the uncompiled content to the DOM and then compiling it.  For example, if a controller in a lazy loaded module calls $element[0].getElementsByTagName('whatever'), IE will invalidated the returned HTMLCollection once the lazy loaded content is added to the DOM (this is not an issue in Firefox or Chrome).  By adding the content and then compiling, we prevent IE from invalidating saved elements.  (This issue was encountered when lazy loading a module that uses angular-material's md-tabs, which saves tab elements.)
